  "text": "In Figure 7 , we show that our framework can also be used for face frontalization. The results of other methods are from paper [CITATION_1] . Unlike other methods our framework is not trained using pose annotations. With a frontal face as the input image to extract attributes, our framework can generate identity preserving frontal faces. Compared with [CITATION_2] , the advantage of our method is that we are able to keep the lighting and skin color.",
